Both sexes.
the following information was not included by Bouček in the original generic description or needed clarification. Both mandibles are confirmed as having three well­separated denticles (Fig. 
9
). Although occipital carina absent, occiput at a different slope from postocciput, the separation between the two abrupt (this more distinct in males). Pronotal collar without posterior smooth strip or row of posteriorly­directed setae (Fig. 
8
); pronotal scrobe open dorsally, such that pronotal collar has a broad middle notch on each side in dorsal view. Forewing basal cell with some scattered setae, basal fold setose; speculum posteriorly closed by a dorsal and ventral row of setae along subcubital fold, and with a few isolated dorsal setae in all specimens; costal cell with a complete ventral row of setae and additional dorsal and ventral setae in apical half. All specimens with only one discernable metatibial spur. Cerci peg­like and exserted.
